JOB-DATA-1: JOB-DATA-1 is a variable that holds multiple lines of JCL (Job Control Language) statements used to define and execute a job in a mainframe environment.

//TRNRPT00 JOB 'TRAN REPORT',CLASS=A,MSGCLASS=0, - Defines the job name, description, class, and message class. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:84: //TRNRPT00 JOB 'TRAN REPORT',CLASS=A,MSGCLASS=0,)
// NOTIFY=&SYSUID - Specifies that a notification will be sent to the user ID associated with the job. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:85: // NOTIFY=&SYSUID)
//* - Denotes a comment line in JCL. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:86: //*)
//JOBLIB JCLLIB ORDER=('AWS.M2.CARDDEMO.PROC') - Specifies the order of libraries to be searched for JCL procedures. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:87: //JOBLIB JCLLIB ORDER=('AWS.M2.CARDDEMO.PROC'))
//STEP10 EXEC PROC=TRANREPT - Executes a procedure named 'TRANREPT'. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:88: //STEP10 EXEC PROC=TRANREPT)
//STEP05R.SYMNAMES DD * - Defines a symbolic name for a dataset. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:89: //STEP05R.SYMNAMES DD *)
TRAN-CARD-NUM,263,16,ZD - Specifies the format and position of the 'TRAN-CARD-NUM' field. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:90: TRAN-CARD-NUM,263,16,ZD)
TRAN-PROC-DT,305,10,CH - Specifies the format and position of the 'TRAN-PROC-DT' field. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:91: TRAN-PROC-DT,305,10,CH)
PARM-START-DATE,C' - Specifies the start date parameter. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:92: PARM-START-DATE,C')
PARM-END-DATE,C' - Specifies the end date parameter. (see app/cbl/CORPT00C.cbl:93: PARM-END-DATE,C')
